---
title: Raw transaction, Mined transaction
---

Raw transaction is determining a hash of input data: function-signature, arguments, nonce, max-gas-price, base-gas-price, etc.

In real, it looks like this:

```json
{
  type: 2,
  chainId: 11155111,
  nonce: 18,
  maxPriorityFeePerGas: BigNumber { _hex: '0x59682f00', _isBigNumber: true },
  maxFeePerGas: BigNumber { _hex: '0x0127617882', _isBigNumber: true },
  gasPrice: null,
  gasLimit: BigNumber { _hex: '0x037153', _isBigNumber: true },
  to: '0xcd1754AD8b7756A63Fb43FA5B8F99b8abe7b76ba',
  value: BigNumber { _hex: '0x34fc96ad9455', _isBigNumber: true },
  data: '',
  accessList: [],
  hash: '0x066f8e724947367a6e7b7fd6433619396ed0b2db5857a11f80450e3a5ef5be13',
  v: 1,
  r: '0x175ca401f1263b7397e9153ba093c7290c6f8e191ccd380a3ab8bc8fc16cdf15',
  s: '0x5d207f65e0f2c8d1a6b2dbfccbfa4f5af5e432785e0466321302e1527f18a2f6',
  from: '0xB751710Af8Ce68677aB960adB103060f38d09714',
  confirmations: 0,
  wait: [Function (anonymous)]
}
```

The code for this:

```ts
const rawTx = await srcToken
    .connect(srcSigner)
    .send(sendParams, messagingFee, srcSigner.address, { value: messagingFee.nativeFee })
const txReceipt = await rawTx.wait()
console.log(
    `Tx hash for sending tokens from contract \'${srcToken.address.slice(0, 6)}...${srcToken.address.slice(-4)}\': \n\t\'${sendTx.hash}\'`
)
console.log(rawTx)
console.log(txReceipt)
```

Main differences:

Raw tx:

- max. gas permissible values (max base, max priority fees)
- no event logs
  
| Topic | Raw Tx | Mined Tx |
|--|--|--|
| Define | Before sending tx | After tx is mined |
| Gas | max. allowed gas values like base, priority fees | actual gas used |
| Event logs | no event logs present in raw tx | event log data (if any) is present |
| Function sig | present | present |
| v, r, s | present | absent |
| nonce | present | abset |
